  "title": "Claim for iPhone Reported Stolen but Later Recovered with Partial Battery and Screen Damage",
  "description": "Customer reported their iPhone stolen and filed a claim under AppleCare+. The device was later recovered; it retains most components but the battery is heavily degraded and the screen assembly is damaged but still intact and functional, showing flickering and touch responsiveness issues. The customer claims the damage occurred following the theft during an unknown handling event.",
  "adjustments": "Modified narrative to indicate the device was recovered with battery degraded yet present, and screen assembly damaged but still intact and partially functional, rather than missing components outright. Damage is described as possibly linked to accidental handling post-recovery, rather than clearly due to theft-related dismantling.",
  "risk_analysis": "By clarifying that the device was returned largely intact with functional albeit impaired essential components, and introducing ambiguity about accidental damage occurring post-theft, this scenario now sits near the boundary between exclusion under Section 4.2(iv) for lost or stolen devices and potential coverage under accidental damage from handling in Section 3.2. The partial operability and presence of major components complicate automatic denial and warrant further evaluation."
}

